reviewText: Only rating provided.
The staff are friendly and professional. The problem is I had a 9:15 appointment and I didn’t see the doctor until 10:40.

Dr. Hamat has forever changed my life after just one visit! He attentively listened to my concerns, and ordered accessible tests to determine the source of my digestive health issues.  The quick results eliminated common diagnosis & confirmed a very rare congenital condition, which is normally identified in children due to digestive discomfort, not in 40 year olds, who have been experiencing symptoms their while lives.  Dr. Hamat’s staff called me with results and explained the process for obtaining the specialty prescription “treatment”, which I’ve been taking for 1 week, and already have had tremendous results, which have absolutely improved my life.

Dr. Hamat’s bedside manner is respectfully compassionate, and he’s open to considering low likelihood, non-invasive testing options to pinpoint an appropriate diagnosis.

His staff are friendly and down to earth, making each appointment feel like you are visiting old friends, rather than the nervousness experienced when visiting many health providers.

Also, there is no wait.  They start their appointments on time, and don’t make you feel rushed as they inquire to your symptoms, but are efficient in processing your needs, such that you can get back to the rest of your life within 1 hour of your appointment.  They are a very well run health provider office, and make their in office patients a priority.

The only area where I would suggest improvement is related to reaching staff when trying to confirm test results, as I had a very difficult time reaching staff between diagnosis and specialty prescription ordering, noting it seems like their automated phone system may have some unexpected errors when routing calls & messages.
Nice staff and excellent care.

I recently was seen at Digestive & Liver Disease Consults. It was my first visit with Dr. Kwak, it put my mind at ease to be in the hands of such a caring professional. In the consultation not only was the best treatment planned out for me. My needs were taken in consideration along with my healing process. For some people that might not be a big deal. However I have come across and left medical practices that do not include me in my healings process. Accompanied by a pleasantly caring staff my first visit with Dr. Kwak was great and most of all productive. I highly recommend this practice to meet your needs.

I've seen Dr Reddy in 2017 and was very happy with what he offered in terms of answers and trying to figure out what was wrong. I just recently started seeing him and Dr. Laura for unrelated issues and I'm upset with the way I have been treated at this location. First, they wanted to schedule an endoscopy and hydrogen breath test in March. They gave me a number to call to schedule. I called 3 times to this number and nobody returned my call. I was dealing with other health issues between April & May & so I waited until May to try and schedule again. I called the main number and they gave me the correct number to the scheduler. So my first complaint is not getting the correct number to schedule the procedure. Next, I'm in pretty bad pain and things got worse. They were able to get me in for an endoscopy pretty quickly so I was happy about that. They told me not to do the Hydrogen Breath Test because I was very nauseous and to wait until after the endoscopy. Okay great. After endoscopy I received paper work that says i have GERD and they gave me instructions on how to eat and medication. Well none of this was working so I messaged and they said continue with the hydrogen breath test. Fast forward to finally having Dr Laura call me, and honestly I left that conversation so upset I hung up on her. She told me I didn't have GERD, THEN WHY IN THE WORLD DID YOU PEOPLE PRESCRIBE ME UNNECESSSARY MEDICATION & TELL ME I DID. (this was not her fault) but I don't understand why Dr. Reddy would say I have GERD if there is no evidence? Then after realizing I couldn't get into to do a hydrogen breath test soon enough (I understand this, doctors are busy and they only have open availability), but I couldn't wait so I was hoping she could at least provide me with relief. She then made a comment that I should've scheduled in March when I originally saw her. Maybe I took that comment the wrong way, but it upset me. I tried to schedule! This office needs to work on their communication and correcting the phone extensions because they take you to the wrong person.

They canceled our appointment last minute with no call or nothing, I tried to call twice prior to the appointment and they would never answer the phone or return my call.  From reading other reviews it looks like this is a common problem for this office.

I have used this facility for the past 7 years, My doctor is Dr. Hammett he is a very good doctor everyone is very good, when it comes to procedure day everyone is great! My complain is after the procedure is done and you need to get a hold of someone at there office they don’t return your call backs you can never get a hold of anyone. I have left over 10 messages still no reply and that’s the only problem that I have been dealing with them over the past 7 years.
They changed my appointment twice day before colonoscopy,  therefore causing me to lose ride and never bothered to call and apologize or reschedule

I am posting this for my sister Billie Jackson regarding her experience with this office.
She had a colonoscopy on 10-29-19, she has an aneurysm on her spleen which could be dangerous during a colonoscopy.  The procedure was scheduled on 10-22 with a follow-up scheduled for 11-12 to get results. The morning of the procedure the office called to change her arrival time twice and a different doctor performed the colonoscopy at the last minute. There were problems with her procedure which were not dealt with professionally at the time.  The office called to confirm her appt. twice and called home number to change it within 15 minutes of appt. time, she was already gone to appt.
Upon arrival for her follow-up she was told she needed to reschedule with the Dr. that ordered the test and that Dr. Shah, who she had been scheduled with, could not give her the results. She was told because she had changed doctors that Dr. Shah could not see her for the appt. and she would need to reschedule with Laura. She asked if she could just get her results. They refused even though both doctors were in the office. She asked to be worked in for 5 minutes to get results as there had been a biopsy done as well. Was told working her in wasn't the issue, that she would need to see correct doctor.  The office changed doctors, not her. As of today she still has not received her results.

If I could give a lower score I would. The first time I saw dr tesfay I was told there was nothing she could do for me I just needed to change my diet. She sent me for sibo text which of course was positive she gave me the exact same antibiotics o told her I had and didn’t work. Had an appointment for today and they tell me it is for a different location?!?!  I did not know they had a different location. Never asked what location etc. humble office says they are charging me a 25.00 fee for no show. NO SHOW?  I was standing right in front of her 10 minutes before my appointment was to start. Just noticed these are not doctors anyway. Just P.A.’s consulting?  Should have known. Not professional at all.
